==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Aristocratical
<hw>Ar`is*to*crat"ic*al</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <?/: cf. F. <ets>aristocratique</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Of or pertaining to an aristocracy; consisting in, or favoring, a
government of nobles, or principal men; <as>as, an <ex>aristocratic</ex>
constitution</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Partaking of aristocracy; befitting aristocracy;
characteristic of, or originating with, the aristocracy; <as>as, an
<ex>aristocratic</ex> measure; <ex>aristocratic</ex> pride or
manners.</as></def> -- <wordforms><wf>Ar`is*to*crat"ic*al*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos> -- <wf>Ar`is*to*crat"ic*al*ness</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aristocratism</ent>⟦br⟧
